---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import ReferralBanner from "../../components/ReferralBanner.astro";
import OnThisPage from "../../components/OnThisPage.astro";
import FaqSchema from "../../components/FaqSchema.astro";

const referralCode = "STAR-FSRJ-5N7Z";
const referralLink = `https://www.robertsspaceindustries.com/enlist?referral=${referralCode}`;
const referralPage = "/star-citizen-referral-code/";

const heroImg = "/assets/img/beginner-tips/scb-beginner-tips-structured-route-hero.webp";
const planningImg = "/assets/img/beginner-tips/scb-beginner-tips-priority-planning.webp";

const faqItems = [
  {
    q: "What should I do first after spawning in?",
    a: "Set your regeneration point immediately, create a minimal repeatable kit, and complete one simple local contract to learn the full loop from acceptance to return."
  },
  {
    q: "Why do beginners lose so much money?",
    a: "Because they over-gear, travel too far, and stack too many objectives in one session. Stability beats ambition early on."
  },
  {
    q: "Should I rush ship upgrades?",
    a: "No. Master one loop first. Income consistency matters more than early hardware upgrades."
  },
  {
    q: "What is the safest first loop?",
    a: "Local delivery or one controlled bunker contract in a single region."
  }
];

const faqJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faqItems.map((item) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: item.q,
    acceptedAnswer: {
      "@type": "Answer",
      text: item.a
    }
  }))
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Star Citizen Beginner Guide – Structured Start Strategy"
  description="A complete in-depth beginner strategy for Star Citizen. Learn structured progression, mission loops, risk control, gear discipline and long-term growth."
  canonicalPath="/beginner-tips/"
>
<link slot="head" rel="preload" as="image" href={heroImg} fetchpriority="high" />

<SiteHeader active="guides" />

<main class="container">

<section class="hero">
  <img
    class="hero__img"
    src={heroImg}
    alt="Structured beginner learning route on a star map"
    loading="eager"
    fetchpriority="high"
    decoding="async"
    width="1536"
    height="1024"
  />
  <div class="hero__overlay"></div>
  <div class="hero__content">
    <div class="homeHero__content">
      <div style="max-width:760px;padding:26px 0;">
        <div class="kicker"><span class="dot"></span> Beginner Guide</div>
        <h1 class="h1">Star Citizen Beginner Strategy</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          This is not a surface checklist. This is a structured progression framework designed to eliminate chaos and accelerate mastery.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<ReferralBanner
  code={referralCode}
  bonus="50,000 UEC"
  ctaHref={referralLink}
  howItWorksHref={`${referralPage}#how-to-use`}
  sublineHtml="Enter during signup or within <b>24 hours</b> after account creation."
  ariaLabel="Referral bonus"
/>

<OnThisPage
  title="Guide Structure"
  items={[
    { label: "Progression model", href: "#progression-model" },
    { label: "Session framework", href: "#session-framework" },
    { label: "Mission loops", href: "#mission-loops" },
    { label: "Risk system", href: "#risk-system" },
    { label: "Economic growth", href: "#economic-growth" },
    { label: "FAQ", href: "#faq" }
  ]}
/>

<section id="progression-model" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">The Beginner Progression Model</h2>

<p>
Most new players fail because they chase content instead of building systems.
Your first objective is stability, not profit.
Your second objective is repeatability.
Only then should you scale income.
</p>

<div class="tableWrap">
<table class="scTable">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Phase</th>
<th>Objective</th>
<th>What changes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>Stabilization</th>
<td>Learn movement, travel, return cycles</td>
<td>Sessions stop feeling chaotic</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Repetition</th>
<td>Run one loop multiple times</td>
<td>Income becomes predictable</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Optimization</th>
<td>Reduce downtime and losses</td>
<td>Profit per hour increases</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Expansion</th>
<td>Add new loop or ship upgrade</td>
<td>Growth compounds</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<section id="session-framework" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">The 3-Session Framework</h2>

<p>
Instead of wandering, use structured sessions.
Each session has a purpose.
</p>

<div class="tableWrap">
<table class="scTable">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Session</th>
<th>Focus</th>
<th>Measured outcome</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>1</th>
<td>Spawn setup and one safe contract</td>
<td>Zero confusion about navigation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>2</th>
<td>Repeat same contract type</td>
<td>Reduced travel errors</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>3</th>
<td>Add minor complexity</td>
<td>Confidence under pressure</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
<div class="grid2">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">Planning Before Profit</h2>

<p>
Most beginners buy gear before they understand loss cycles.
Plan your baseline kit.
Plan your route.
Plan your recovery path.
</p>

<p>
Structure creates confidence.
Confidence creates efficiency.
Efficiency creates income.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card pad">
<img
class="imgRounded"
src={planningImg}
alt="Priority planning board for beginner pilot"
loading="lazy"
decoding="async"
width="1536"
height="1024"
/>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section id="mission-loops" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">First Mission Loop Selection</h2>

<div class="tableWrap">
<table class="scTable">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Loop</th>
<th>Teaches</th>
<th>Risk level</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>Delivery</th>
<td>Navigation, landing discipline</td>
<td>Low</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Local bunker</th>
<td>Combat fundamentals</td>
<td>Medium</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Salvage practice</th>
<td>Ship positioning, scanning</td>
<td>Low to medium</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<section id="risk-system" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">Risk Budget System</h2>

<p>
Never carry more value than the mission justifies.
Risk is a multiplier.
If risk grows faster than skill, progression collapses.
</p>

<div class="tableWrap">
<table class="scTable">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Loadout type</th>
<th>When to use</th>
<th>Why</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>Baseline kit</th>
<td>Default runs</td>
<td>Fast recovery</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Enhanced kit</th>
<td>Controlled missions</td>
<td>Higher success rate</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>High value kit</th>
<td>Advanced content</td>
<td>High risk high reward</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<section id="economic-growth" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">Economic Scaling Strategy</h2>

<p>
Income growth is about downtime reduction.
The player who completes three clean loops beats the player who attempts one large risky run.
</p>

<p>
When stable, transition into:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Higher tier bunker contracts</li>
<li>Refined trading routes</li>
<li>Specialized FPS loops</li>
<li>Ship role specialization</li>
</ul>

</div>
</section>

<section id="faq" class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq">
{faqItems.map((item) => (
<details class="faqItem">
<summary class="faqQ">{item.q}</summary>
<div class="faqA">{item.a}</div>
</details>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
<div class="card pad">
<h2 class="section__title">Next Steps</h2>
<div class="btnrow">
<a class="btn primary" href={referralLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Create Account (Code prefilled)</a>
<a class="btn secondary" href="/starter-pack-guide/">Starter Pack Guide</a>
<a class="btn secondary" href="/best-settings/">Best Settings</a>
<a class="btn secondary" href="/earn-auec-fast/">Earn aUEC Fast</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<FaqSchema json={faqJsonLd} />

<footer class="footer">
<div class="footer__inner">
<div class="footer__brand">SCB — Unofficial Star Citizen guide.</div>
<div class="footer__legal">
Not affiliated with Cloud Imperium Games or Roberts Space Industries.
</div>
</div>
</footer>

</main>
</BaseLayout>
